## Technical Architecture

### Directory Structure
```
.purr/
├── index          # Binary index file (staged files metadata)
├── objects/       # Blob storage (SHA-1 named files)
│   ├── ab/
│   │   └── cdef...
│   └── ...
├── refs/
│   └── heads/     # Branch references
└── logs/          # Operation logs
```

### Index Format
- **Header:** 12 bytes
  - Magic: `"DIRC"` (4 bytes)
  - Version: `2` (4 bytes, big-endian)
  - Entry count (4 bytes, big-endian)
- **Entries:** Variable length per file
  - Metadata: 62 bytes (timestamps, permissions, size, SHA-1, etc.)
  - Path length: 2 bytes
  - Path data: variable
  - Padding: aligned to 8-byte boundary

### Blob Format (Git-compatible)
- Header: `blob <size>\0`
- Content: raw file data
- Storage: zlib-compressed
- Naming: First 2 chars of SHA-1 as directory, rest as filename

